Armed with this knowledge a coder will set to and start the learning process that goes into understanding any new technology. Being successful in this business is not as much about how quick you can learn to code, or even how well you can code, it's about how quickly you can adapt to new emerging technologies while keeping an appropriate hand in the history and understanding where this stuff came from. The first part will keep you ahead of the game and keep you thinking and planning your implementations out with the future in mind, while the second part will give you the right mindset for picking up and integrating with the mountains of legacy code and functionality that exists out there in the real world.

